Package it.polimi.ingsw.client.cli

Class PrinterIslands

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.client.cli.PrinterIslands
public class PrinterIslands extends Object
Class for printing LinkedIslands We have chosen to print students only on the main islands Therefore, when an island is joined to another, the printing will be made only on the second one The towers will be printed on all islands regardless of their type the printing is done on the two sides of the islands in the first side, the first two spaces are reserved for the printing of the tower and possibly of mother nature

      private void side(boolean connected, boolean middle, Tower tower)

    • side

      private void side(boolean connected, boolean middle, IslandCardDto island, int indexIsland, int maxSize)
      Prints the side of the island depending on whether the island is connected or not Called only if the island is a main island
      Parameters:
      connected - is true if the island is connected with the next one
      middle - is true if the island is connected with the previous one and the next one
      island - the island to print
      indexIsland - the index of the island to print
      maxSize - is 5 if it's the first side, 7 if it's the second one. represents the number of students that can be printed on that line

    • printIslandContent

      private void printIslandContent(IslandCardDto island, int indexIsland, int maxSize)
      Prints the content of the island If the max size is 5, it prints, in order, mother nature, the tower and max five students If the max size is 7, it prints the remaining students, if any
      Parameters:
      island - the island to print
      indexIsland - the index of the island to print
      maxSize - is 5 if it's the first side, 7 if it's the second one.
